title.narrative: EARLY CHILDHOOD DEVELOPMENT

description.narrative: Strengthened national frameworks, policies, plans and standards to increase access to high-quality, equitable, inclusive, and holistic early Early Child Development (ECD), learning and care environments for girls and boys (0-8 years) and their families by 2021, including in emergencies, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Early Learning, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, all boys, girls and adolescents, especially the most disadvantaged among them, have improved their education and developmental outcomes and access equitable and inclusive learning environments across the life cycle, including in emergencies.

title.narrative: Strengthened national frameworks, policies, plans and standards to increase access to high-quality, equitable, inclusive, andholistic early ECD, learning and care environments for girls and boys (0-8 years) and their families by 2021, including inemergencies

description.narrative: Through technical and financial assistance,UNICEF ECA collaborated with governments, national, and regional partners to enhance the knowledge and the skills of 5,525 parents, ECD practitioners, teachers, and other caregivers to provide approximately 27,415 girls and boys under 8 years with nurturing care, learning, and holistic development in safe, protective, and enriching environments. Capacity building, advocacy and partnerships were major strategies that were successfully employed in advancing policy initiatives for inclusive ECD, the provision of developmentally appropriate curriculum, and quality environments for nurturing care and early learning in homes, ECD centres, and schools. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
